rComments: I don't even know where to begin... this professor is extremely disorganized and has his own "philosophy" which does not agree with university policy which resulted in a last minute change in the syllabus. NO instructions provided for the assignments worth 2/3 of your grade, i even attended every single lecture... I would avoid him at all costs!!

Got an A-. But I did I learn anything? Nope. The assignments saved me, 'cause God knows I had no idea what was going on in lecture or the midterm/exam. This is probably because assignments are marked by the TA's and not an insane little man. Use the textbook- it'll probably teach you more than anything else in that course.
Learned nothing.
Funny and nice person. listen and study and you will get an A.
He did not stop on topic once and to make it worse he blind sided the class with his exam in which he had to remark because everyone failed.
He just repeats himself over and over about normal distribution and when he teaches something new he doesn't explain it well at all. Easy because assignments and midterms all on same thing

Was not very helpful whenever I asked him for help. Seemed very patronizing students at times, especially when they asked for help pertaining to his lectures. Routinely stopped class when students were late, left early or were talking.

This man is satan. He disrespects students, has no communication skills. He is simply ridiculous to the point of insanity. He is rude and responds to all questions with "what a stupid question" with in incomprehensible Indian accent.

HE IS NOT MEAN OR RUDE. That is just the method he uses to teach and train his students.Often, students ask senseless questions, and Suko doesn't directly give you an answer, but he makes you think first so you can remember. He is a very knowledagable prof, just respect him and listen to what he says, you will do well. There are TAs to help as well
He's a nice guy -give him a break. He tries his best and he's very cute. He has a strong passion for statistics and he will try his best to help you.

I found him to be a pretty good teacher. I understood the material well (the material wasn't that hard). The only problem I had with him was his reluctance to answer questions- he was often very rude when doing so.

Very underrated prof. He did not give feedback on midterm because  you were allowed to resubmit it.  If people weren't too busy hating on the professor they might actually learn something and realize he actually has a warm sense of humor. One of the most misunderstood profs. One thing for sure is you definitely learn the basics in this class.

Very frustrating class, I had to drag myself to it everytime. From Sept - mid Nov he taught 4 chapters, reptitious, then tried to cram 4 chapters into 2 weeks leading up to the final exam. If it weren't for TAs you would get no help. He lectured on how to be students, singled people out if they got up to go to washroom or came in late.

Terrible prof. Repeats himself on a daily basis. Don't bother asking questions, he will just condescend you and refuse to answer. He doesn't cover much material in comparisson to other sections. The assignments and exams are pretty easy. All open book and gives the questions in advance. Method of correction is however questionable.
cannot understand him to good, but his midterms and assignment are easy. everythign is usually open book
Ridiculous  teacher who criticizes students with disabilities and who assignments don't make any sense

He teaches different but if you just finish the assignments you should be fine. His exams were funny cause there is no wrong answer so as long as you support yourself you should be fine! He wants people to go to his dissicusion groups and if he remebers your face you will get good marks. Dont buy the textbook..just photocopy.I got a A- so im happy!
Worst prof I have ever had.   Makes no sense... has no structure and goes all over the place. Impossible to follow. Knows his stuff, but cannont communicate AT ALL.

It is too bad that Suko can not get the message across, otherwise i would have learned something. It is obvious that he tries to get the message across, but when it doesnt, what point does he serve anyway. The text proves more useful than Suko could ever be to this course.

this guy knows his stuff. dont complain , he tries his best, and goes at a very slow pace for students ... this is not your typical hardcore stats class anyway, the material is straightforward and his sense of humour is one of a kind

Suko's one of the most underrated and misunderstood profs I've ever come across. He's actually got a warm sense of humor that many mistake for rude sarcasm.  Don't take the class if you're looking to be entertained, but if you're serious about learning stats from a more theoretical perspective then by all means do!  An excellent teacher !
He knows his stuff; it's just too bad he won't help you learn...people like this should not be teaching

Suko sucks.  He's very insulting and verbally abusive.  He is very unhelpful, he will not answer questions, nor tell you what he wants on assignments.  If I pass this course it will be by the grace of God.

this class was complete useless. suko is brilliant but hasnt a clue how to teach. I spent the last 3 days b4 the final reading online textbooks and trying to teach the second half of the term to myself. He is very unclear and confusing and as smart as he is ...he should no longer be teaching.
No Comments
Wow...it's a good thing I bought the text 'cause I didn't understand a word he said!
Hard and stressful course but he'll pass you.  I want you to appreciate this.
